article.headline: Missouri St. 79, Tenn.-Martin 51
article.story: SPRINGFIELD, Mo. -- Three Missouri State players finished with 13 points in a 79-51 rout of Tennessee-Martin on Wednesday night. Missouri State (8-0) shot 80 percent in the first 6:31 to pull away from the Skyhawks (1-6), who never led. The Bears shot 54.1 percent in the first half and led 50-27 at halftime. A 3-pointer by Reuben Clayton with 16:46 left got Tennessee-Martin within 53-36, the closest it got the rest of the way. Jermaine Mallett, Kyle Weems and Adam Leonard all had 13 for Missouri State. Leonard was 5-for-5 from the field in the first half, including 3-for-3 from beyond the 3-point line. Nafis Ricks added 11 for Missouri State. Delrico Lane and Clayton each had 15 for Tennessee-Martin.
